[style name="KillerText"]
How to Secure a House - By Martin Seeder (Bestseller)
Chapter One\: When defending your most valueable possesions, one should store the key in a discreet object at the front of their house. No one would suspect a thing there!
In order to unlock said item, scatter a number of SPECIAL keys across your property.
One should force the intruder to partake in puzzles that are enourmously difficult.
A few examples are, hiding it in a room behind several boulders, tiptoing across an attic, or even a mechanical contraption! Just force them to look all over the house!
(End of Book)
